---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const title = `Surrogate Story | ${SITE_TITLE}`;
const description = 'A compelling look at the surrogacy case that challenged law, biology, and the meaning of parenthood.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
		<style>
			:root {
				--font-display: 'Playfair Display', serif;
				--font-body: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
			}

			body {
				font-family: var(--font-body);
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f5f5f7 0%, #ffffff 50%, #f0f0f5 100%);
				color: #0f1219;
				margin: 0;
			}

			main {
				width: min(100%, 1120px);
				max-width: calc(100% - 2.5rem);
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 2rem 0 4rem;
			}

			.hero {
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f1219 0%, #1a1f2e 50%, #2d1b4e 100%);
				color: white;
				padding: 4rem 2rem;
				border-radius: 32px;
				text-align: center;
				margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
			}

			.hero h1 {
				font-family: var(--font-display);
				font-size: clamp(2.15rem, 3.6vw, 3rem);
				margin: 0 0 1rem;
				letter-spacing: -0.03em;
			}

			.hero p {
				margin: 0 auto;
				max-width: 720px;
				font-size: 1.05rem;
				line-height: 1.8;
				color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
			}

			.content {
				display: grid;
				gap: 1.5rem;
				grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
				align-items: start;
			}

			.panel {
				background: rgba(255,255,255,0.94);
				border: 1px solid rgba(35,55,255,0.08);
				border-radius: 24px;
				padding: 2rem;
				box-shadow: 0 16px 40px rgba(15,18,25,0.08);
			}

			.panel h2 {
				font-family: var(--font-display);
				font-size: 1.45rem;
				margin: 0 0 1rem;
			}

			.panel p {
				font-size: 1rem;
				line-height: 1.8;
				color: rgba(15,18,25,0.78);
				margin: 0 0 1rem;
			}

			.quote {
				font-size: 1.05rem;
				font-weight: 600;
				color: #2337ff;
				padding-left: 1rem;
				border-left: 3px solid #2337ff;
				margin-top: 1.2rem;
			}

			/* Dark mode for panels */
			.dark .panel {
				background: rgba(17,24,39,0.95);
				border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
				box-shadow: 0 14px 40px rgba(2,6,23,0.6);
			}

			.dark .panel h2 {
				color: #f9fafb;
			}

			.dark .panel p {
				color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
			}

			.dark .quote {
				color: #8db4ff;
				border-left-color: rgba(139,180,255,0.18);
				background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
				padding-left: 1rem;
			}

			/* Prevent images from zooming in dark mode */
			.panel img {
				max-width: 100%;
				height: auto;
				object-fit: contain;
				transform: none !important;
				scale: 1 !important;
				transition: none !important;
			}

			.dark .panel img {
				transform: none !important;
				scale: 1 !important;
				filter: none !important;
			}

			@media (max-width: 860px) {
				.content {
					grid-template-columns: 1fr;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section class="hero">
				<h1>Surrogate Story</h1>
				<p>
					When love, law, and legacy collided, the case became more than a legal battle; it became
					a defining moment about family, identity, and parenthood.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="content">
				<article class="panel">
					<h2>Family, law, and legacy</h2>
					<p>
						What began as a bitter divorce and an emotionally charged dispute became a precedent-shaping
						case that challenged the way America thinks about parenthood.
					</p>
					<p>
						The question was simple and profound: who is a parent when biology and intention point in
						different directions? The answer would reshape lives and define a new conversation about family.
					</p>
					<div class="quote">Love may be the foundation of family, but the law still has to decide who gets to call it home.</div>
				</article>

				<article class="panel">
					<h2>Why it matters</h2>
					<p>
						This story explores the emotional and legal stakes behind one of the most consequential cases
						of its time, revealing the human cost beneath the headlines.
					</p>
					<p>
						It is a story about identity, intent, and the extraordinary ways people fight for the children
						and futures they believe belong to them.
					</p>
				</article>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
